# Section 2 — Advantages of Cloud Computing

This section explains why so many companies are moving to the cloud.  
Cloud computing offers six major advantages that help organizations reduce costs, increase agility, and innovate faster.

---

## ## Advantage #1 — Trade Capital Expense for Variable Expense

Traditional IT requires large **capital expenses (capex)** to buy, install, and maintain physical hardware.  
You pay for the entire data center whether you use it or not.

With cloud computing, costs become **variable expenses**:
- You pay **only when you consume resources**
- You pay **only for the amount you use**
- No upfront investment in servers or data centers
- Capacity can be added in **minutes**, not weeks

This reduces maintenance and allows teams to focus on core business goals instead of managing hardware.

---

## ## Advantage #2 — Benefit from Massive Economies of Scale

Economies of scale > Cloud providers like AWS aggregate usage from **hundreds of thousands of customers**.  
This large scale allows them to:
- Operate more efficiently  
- Reduce per‑unit costs  
- Offer **lower pay‑as‑you‑go prices** than most companies can achieve on their own  

Organizations benefit directly from these economies of scale.

---

## ## Advantage #3 — Stop Guessing Capacity

In traditional environments, you must guess how much capacity you will need:
- Guess too high → expensive idle resources  
- Guess too low → insufficient performance  

With cloud computing:
- You can scale **up or down** at any time  
- You get exactly the capacity you need  
- Scaling happens in **minutes**  

Capacity planning becomes simple and risk‑free.

---

## ## Advantage #4 — Increase Speed and Agility

In the cloud, new IT resources are available **with just a click**.  
This reduces provisioning time from **weeks to minutes**.

As a result:
- Developers can experiment faster  
- Innovation becomes cheaper and easier  
- Organizations gain significant agility  

The cloud dramatically accelerates development and deployment cycles.

---

## ## Advantage #5 — Stop Spending Money on Running and Maintaining Data Centers

> NOT a benefit of cloud computing (racking, stacking, powering servers)

Cloud computing removes the need to:
- Operate physical data centers  
- Maintain hardware  
- Handle power, cooling, and physical security  

Instead, teams can focus on:
- Building applications  
- Improving customer experience  
- Delivering business value  

AWS handles the heavy lifting of infrastructure management.

---

## ## Advantage #6 — Go Global in Minutes

With AWS, you can deploy applications to **multiple Regions worldwide** in just a few clicks.

This enables:
- Lower latency for global customers  
- Better user experience  
- Fast and cost‑effective international expansion  

Going global becomes simple and accessible for any organization.

---

# ## Key Takeaways — Section 2

The six advantages of cloud computing are:

- Trade capital expense for variable expense  
- Massive economies of scale  
- Stop guessing capacity  
- Increase speed and agility  
- Stop spending money on running and maintaining data centers  
- Go global in minutes  

