# Sample Exam Question — Module Review

## Question
Why is AWS more economical than traditional data centers for applications with varying compute workloads?

### Choices
A. Amazon EC2 costs are billed on a monthly basis  
B. Customers retain full administrative access to their Amazon EC2 instances  
C. Amazon EC2 instances can be launched on-demand when needed  
D. Customers can permanently run enough instances to handle peak workloads  

---

## Correct Answer: **C**

### Explanation
AWS is more economical because **EC2 instances can be launched on-demand**, meaning you only pay for compute capacity when you actually need it.  
This avoids the cost of maintaining idle servers and supports variable workloads efficiently.

---
### Why AWS is more economical
- Pay only for what you use
- Stop guessing capacity
- Scale on demand
